    "custom_liquid_wxq3rE": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Custom Liquid - what you can do in HA",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "{% comment %}\n  Konnected – Two‑Column Snapshot for Home Assistant users  \n  Focus on “What You Can Do in Home Assistant”\n{% endcomment %}\n\n<section class=\"konnected‑ha‑glance\">\n  <div class=\"page-width\">\n    <h2 class=\"h2 text-center heading\">What You Can Do in Home Assistant</h2>\n\n    <div class=\"glance-grid\">\n      <!-- Alarm Panel Pro Kits -->\n      <div class=\"glance-card\">\n        <h2 class=\"card-title\"><center><big>Home Assistant Alarm Panel</big></center></h2>\n        <p class=\"card-blurb\">\n          <strong>Convert your wired sensors into smart Home Assistant entities</strong>  \n          so you can monitor, arm, and automate from within HA itself.\n        </p>\n\n        <ul class=\"mini-bullets\">\n          <li>Make each zone a Home Assistant binary or sensor entity</li>\n          <li>Trigger automations like “arm when last one leaves” or “light + siren on breach”</li>\n          <li>Panel can run local alarm logic so HA outages don’t disable alerts</li>\n          <li>Full compatibility with ESPHome and HA’s alarm integration</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Garage Door Opener Kits -->\n      <div class=\"glance-card\">\n        <h2 class=\"card-title\"><center><big>Home Assistant Garage Control</big></center></h2>\n        <p class=\"card-blurb\">\n          <strong>Turn your existing garage opener into a HA “cover” or switch</strong>  \n          so you can control and monitor it directly in your smart home dashboard.\n        </p>\n\n        <ul class=\"mini-bullets\">\n          <li>Expose open/close state as an entity in Home Assistant</li>\n          <li>Trigger actions like “close after dark” or “notify if open too long”</li>\n          <li>Works reliably under HA’s “cover” integration in ESPHome</li>\n          <li>No cloud required - local control, no required monthly fees</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <style>\n    .konnected‑ha‑glance     { margin: 3rem 0; }\n    .glance-grid             { display: grid; gap: 1.5rem;\n                               grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px,1fr)); }\n    .card-title              { margin: 0 0 1.25rem;\n                               font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 600; color:#2563eb; }\n    .card-blurb              { margin: 0; font-size: 2rem; line-height: 1.4; color:#374151; }\n    .glance-card             { background:#fff; border:1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius:12px;\n                               padding: 2rem 2.25rem; }\n    .mini-bullets            { margin: 1rem 0 0; padding: 0; list-style: none;\n                               font-size: 1.6rem; line-height: 1.35; color:#374151; }\n    .mini-bullets li         { position: relative; padding-left: 1.8rem; margin: .4rem 0; }\n    .mini-bullets li::before { content: \"✓\"; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;\n                               font-size: 1.6rem; color:#3b82f6; font-weight: 600; }\n\n    @media (max-width: 640px) {\n      .card-title      { font-size: 1.6rem; }\n      .card-blurb      { font-size: 1.4rem; }\n      .mini-bullets    { font-size: 1.3rem; }\n      .mini-bullets li::before { font-size: 1.3rem; }\n    }\n  </style>\n</section>",
        "color_scheme": "background-2",
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 4
      }
    },
    "custom_liquid_DmNaTA": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Custom Liquid - What's Possible with Automations",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "{% comment %}\n  Konnected – What's Possible with Home Assistant + Konnected\n  Left: Alarm Panel automations\n  Right: Garage Door automations\n{% endcomment %}\n\n<section class=\"konnected-whats-possible\">\n  <div class=\"page-width\" style=\"max-width: 1200px; margin: 3rem auto; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 2rem; justify-content: center;\">\n    \n    <!-- Alarm Panel Use Cases (left) -->\n    <div class=\"possible-card\" style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 300px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem;\">\n      <h2 class=\"card-title\" style=\"font-size: 2.25rem; color: #2563eb; margin-bottom: 1rem;\">Smart Alarm Panel Automations</h2>\n      <p style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #374151; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\">\n        With Konnected and Home Assistant, your wired sensors become more than just passive security – they become active participants in your smart home.\n      </p>\n      <ul class=\"use-bullets\" style=\"list-style: none; padding: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.4; color: #374151; position: relative;\">\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Auto-arm when everyone leaves:</strong> Trigger alarm arming using phone presence, BLE tracking, or occupancy sensors.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Light and siren response to break-ins:</strong> Flash smart lights, activate sirens, lock doors, and notify everyone if a zone is tripped while armed.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Night mode routines tied to disarm:</strong> Disarming at night can dim lights, shut blinds, or set HVAC to sleep settings.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Grace periods and conditional entry delays:</strong> Automate different delays for entry based on time of day or who’s home.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Local logic fallback:</strong> ESPHome-based panels can still run basic alarm logic even if Home Assistant goes offline.</li>\n        <li><strong>Sensor-aware reminders:</strong> Send a warning or postpone arming if any zone (like the back door) is left open.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Garage Door Use Cases (right) -->\n    <div class=\"possible-card\" style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 300px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem;\">\n      <h2 class=\"card-title\" style=\"font-size: 2.25rem; color: #2563eb; margin-bottom: 1rem;\">Smart Garage Automations</h2>\n      <p style=\"font-size: 1.6rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #374151; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\">\n        Your garage can do a lot more than open and close – with Konnected and Home Assistant, it becomes a smart access point you can monitor and automate.\n      </p>\n      <ul class=\"use-bullets\" style=\"list-style: none; padding: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.4; color: #374151; position: relative;\">\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Auto-close after inactivity:</strong> Automatically shut the garage if it’s been open too long – great for peace of mind or forgetful teens.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Geo-triggered opening:</strong> Open the garage as you arrive home using GPS, Wi-Fi, or BLE presence tracking.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Sunset and storm automations:</strong> Ensure the garage is closed after dark or when bad weather is approaching.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Dashboard and voice control:</strong> Monitor status and operate the garage from your HA dashboard or via smart speakers.</li>\n        <li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.8rem;\"><strong>Security coordination:</strong> Automatically close the garage if the alarm is armed or trigger alerts if it’s opened unexpectedly.</li>\n        <li><strong>Sensor-aware climate control:</strong> Prevent the HVAC from kicking on if the garage door is open to avoid wasting energy.</li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <style>\n    .use-bullets li::before {\n      content: \"✓\";\n      position: absolute;\n      left: -1.5rem;\n      color: #3b82f6;\n      font-weight: 600;\n    }\n  </style>\n</section>",
        "color_scheme": "background-2",
        "padding_top": 4,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
